                    <heading>Defence</heading>
                    <p id="GR.DIR.616">
          Greece returned to the military structure of the 
          <xr pageref="N" ref="NATO.IO">North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)</xr>
           in 1980, after an ab­sence of six years. Military service is compulsory, and lasts for nine months. As assessed at November 2023, the armed forces numbered 132,200 (including conscripts), with an army of 93,500, a navy of 16,700 and an air force of some 22,000; in addition, there were some 7,4000 gendarmerie and paramilitary forces. Reservists totalled 289,000, including a national guard of 38,000.
        </p>
